The Herald WARRIORS Midfielder Kuda Mahachi has been suspended by his South African side SuperSport after the Zimbabwean international was accused of physically abusing his four-year-old son. In a statement, SuperSport said they have suspended Mahachi from all club football activities with immediate effect and advised the player to attend to his family and the allegations against him. Mahachi is alleged to have scalded his four-year-old son with water, resulting in the child suffering third degree burns on the head and feet. Reports say part of the boy’s right foot was amputated as a result of the severe burns. The matter is understood to be before the courts. — ZBC.